import LeanFormalization.FullCubicScaffold

/-!
# Required: constant-gamma endpoint

When all five c-coefficients vanish, gamma=1 and Delta is the ordinary plane
Jacobian bracket of alpha and beta.  No external low-degree Keller theorem is
needed: the endpoint reduces to one exact fixed-collision certificate.

If a normalized cubic Keller pair G has a collision G(P)=G(0)=0 with P≠0,
choose M∈GL₂ with M e₂=P and put H(x)=M⁻¹G(Mx).  Then DH(0)=I, J(H)=1,
and H(e₂)=H(0)=0.  Thus full GL₂ conjugation removes the symbolic collision
parameter entirely; the originating script's unfinished `(1,p)` calculation
is unnecessary.

The fixed collision equations give a02=-a03 and b02=-1-b03.  Substitution into
the fourteen nonconstant Jacobian coefficients produces the exact 14-equation,
12-variable system generated by `scripts/endpoint_fixed_collision.py`:

  SHA-256 ec0c43f09dbedfa5d4734c9f96a12e1af946627843a39f6cd1b7b8062e81c935

SymPy 1.14.0 verifies that this ideal is the unit ideal over ℚ.  Public CI run
29869875334 extracted and independently verified the Singular lift witness.
The resulting `MixedGammaCertificates.ConstantGammaE2.no_solution` theorem is
now generated and kernel-checked in
`LeanFormalization/Certificates/ConstantGammaE2.lean`.

The coefficient bridge is also now kernel-checked: the theorem
`MixedGammaFull.ConstantGamma.fixed_collision_impossible` in
`LeanFormalization/ConstantGammaFixedCollision.lean` starts from
`FullCubicScaffold.delta x = 1`, obtains the literal 27-equation `RawSystem`,
specializes gamma to one, derives all fourteen certificate equations, and
applies the generated `no_solution` theorem.

Remaining formalization obligations:
1. affine translation and jet renormalization of an arbitrary collision;
2. the full GL₂ fixed-vector conjugation above;
3. transfer from injectivity of the plane pair to injectivity of the scaffold.
-/

namespace MixedGammaFull.ConstantGamma

open FullCubicScaffold

variable {K : Type*} [Field K] [CharZero K] [IsAlgClosed K]

-- theorem constant_gamma_endpoint ... := by sorry

end MixedGammaFull.ConstantGamma
